OL,3,CDoctors, teachers and soldiers to be
OL,4,Cawarded above-inflation pay rise
OL,6,FThe increases, which were recommended
OL,7,Fby independent pay review bodies, are
OL,8,Fabove the rate of inflation, which
OL,9,Fjumped to 3.5% in April, up from 2.6%
OL,10,Fin March and the highest since January
OL,11,F2024.
OL,13,FReports recently suggested ministers
OL,14,Fhad only budgeted for a 2.8% rise for
OL,15,FNHS and teaching staff, with
OL,16,Fsuggestions that any further cash
OL,17,Fwould have to come from squeezes in
OL,18,Fdepartmental spending.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
