OL,3,CDoctors, teachers and soldiers to be
OL,4,Cawarded above-inflation pay rise
OL,6,FElsewhere, most members of the armed
OL,7,Fforces will be given a 4.5% pay rise,
OL,8,Faccording to Defence Secretary John
OL,9,FHealey, while senior members of the
OL,10,Fmilitary will receive a 3.75% rise.
OL,12,FSenior civil servants will get a 3.25%
OL,13,Fpay rise, according to the Cabinet
OL,14,FOffice, but ministers plan to defer
OL,15,Frolling out new pay bands as part of a
OL,16,Freview of salaries in the upper
OL,17,Fechelons of the Civil Service.
