OL,3,CDoctors, teachers and soldiers to be
OL,4,Cawarded above-inflation pay rise
OL,6,FMeanwhile, doctors are already
OL,7,Fthreatening strike action following
OL,8,Fthe announcement of the 4% pay rise,
OL,9,Fwith Professor Philip Banfield,
OL,10,Fchairman of council at the British
OL,11,FMedical Association (BMA), claiming
OL,12,Fthat the rise does not go far enough
OL,13,Fin restoring historical pay.
OL,15,F"Doctors' pay is still around a
OL,16,Fquarter less than it was in real terms
OL,17,F16 years ago and today's 'award'
OL,18,Fdelays pay restoration even more,
OL,19,Fwithout a Government plan or
OL,20,Freassurance to correct this erosion of
OL,21,Fwhat a doctor is worth," he said.
